<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: BONSALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An accident claimed the life of a 44-year-old man early Sunday, authorities 
reported. 
</P>
<P>
William Trkja of Escondido was killed when his car left the road and flipped 
over on West Lilac Road, east of Camino Del Rey, at 2:20 a.m., said Charles 
Kelley of the coroner's office. 
</P>
<P>
The man, who was thrown from the car, was pronounced dead at the scene, Kelley 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Trkja's car was going about 70 m.p.h. when he lost control on a curve, said 
Kelley. 
</P>
</TEXT>
