<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: ESCONDIDO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A hit-and-run driver struck and killed a pedestrian in Escondido, the coroner's 
office reported Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
Patricia M. Hanrahan, 35, was walking with her disabled bicycle on North Center 
City Parkway near Ivy Dell Lane when she was struck by a car at 11:30 p.m. 
Saturday. She was pronounced dead at the scene. 
</P>
<P>
The California Highway Patrol later arrested a driver in connection with the 
accident, said coroner's deputy Charles Kelley. The CHP would not release the 
identity of the driver. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA081489-0013 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 94491 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
August 14, 1989, Monday, San Diego County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
