<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: POP/ROCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and international 
news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Imprisoned soul singer James Brown has lost the 20 days off he had earned for 
good behavior after officials found $40,600 in cash and checks in his Columbia, 
S.C., jail cell, authorities said. Inmates are allowed no more than $50 in the 
prison. Corrections officials took $600 of the cash for the Inmate Welfare Fund 
and the Internal Revenue Service has already spoken for the rest, saying it 
will be applied to an $11-million lien against Brown. The soul singer is 
serving a six-year term for assault and leading lawmen on a high-speed chase. 
</P>
