<TEXT>
<P>
Britain's weekly tabloid, the News of the World, published an apology to Clint 
Eastwood on Sunday and said it had agreed to pay a large sum in libel damages 
for articles published July 9 under the headline "Go On Clint, Make My Day." 
The amount of damages was not disclosed, but Eastwood, famous for his film 
roles as a laconic Western "tough guy," told reporters he would donate the 
money to charity. 
