<P>
The state Office of Emergency Services lifted a five-day earthquake advisory 
for San Francisco, saying the likelihood of another earthquake in the area 
shaken last week has returned to normal. Shortly after a strong quake jolted 
the Bay Area on Tuesday, the office warned that the chances of another 
earthquake in the same area would be increased for the next five days. There 
were several aftershocks to the magnitude 5.1 earthquake, which caused some 
damage and was blamed for one death, but no new shakers. 
