<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOAT SINKS AFTER FIRE IGNITES PROPANE TANK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SANTA CATALINA ISLAND 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fire swept through a 40-foot boat owned by an FBI agent Sunday, setting off 
about 500 rounds of ammunition before a propane tank exploded and sank the 
vessel. 
</P>
<P>
Seven people aboard the power boat Quentgalic jumped ship and were picked up by 
another boat about three miles from Avalon Bay after smoke began pouring from 
the cabin, Los Angeles County sheriff's deputies said. 
</P>
<P>
"We were just laying up on the top of our deck and we smelled something 
smoking," said Stephanie Los, 21, whose father Stan, an FBI agent, owns the 
vessel. 
</P>
<P>
Los said the group was en route to San Pedro after vacationing on the island. 
</P>
<P>
Los said the fire set off about 500 rounds of ammunition for several firearms 
that were kept on the vessel. 
</P>
<P>
Fire boats sprayed the vessel with water, but flames reached a propane tank and 
it exploded, causing the vessel to sink. 
</P>
