<HEADLINE>
<P>
NIIZEKI BEATS FUJIKI IN NIKKEI GOLF PLAYOFF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NIRAYAMAMACHI, Japan 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Yoshimi Niizeki beat Saburo Fujiki on the first hole of a sudden-death playoff 
Sunday and won the $429,000 Nikkei Cup golf tournament. 
</P>
<P>
In the playoff, Niizeki made a par on the 559-yard, par-5 18th hole to edge 
Fujiki. 
</P>
</TEXT>
