<TEXT>
<P>
Drexel to Pay Arkansas Fine: Drexel Burnham Lambert Inc. has agreed to pay a 
$100,000 fine to the Arkansas Securities Department even though the government 
said it has no evidence that the firm did anything wrong in the state. The 
consent order stems from the possibility that Drexel's Beverly Hills junk bond 
department might have committed improper trades in Arkansas from 1984 through 
1986. Drexel said it would pay the $100,000 even though it hasn't had an office 
in Arkansas for four or five years. 
</P>
