<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST: ANAHEIM; 
</P>
<P>
WOUNDED MAN FOUND AT END OF TRAIL OF BLOOD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man was found unconscious and suffering from a gunshot wound behind an 
Anaheim apartment complex early Sunday after police followed a trail of blood 
from a nearby motel. 
</P>
<P>
Joseph Phillip Sanchez, 24, of Anaheim was found with a gunshot wound that 
severed an artery in his right arm, an Anaheim police spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
Sanchez was taken to UCI Medical Center in Orange, where he was reported in 
serious condition. 
</P>
<P>
Police responded to a report of a shooting at the Tropic Motel, 899 S. Harbor 
Blvd. They found broken windows in two rooms and a trail of blood that lead 
them to Sanchez, who was found behind an apartment complex in the 600 block of 
West Vermont Street, the spokesman said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
