6 E. GERMAN OPERA MEMBERS DEFECT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LONDON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Six members of a leading East German opera company have defected after a 
two-week tour in London, it was reported today. 
</P>
<P>
The Daily Express said the six singers and technicians from the Komische Oper 
had been in hiding in London since their last performance at the Royal Opera 
House on Saturday and planned to leave soon for West Germany. 
</P>
<P>
The East German Embassy refused any comment. 
</P>
