<P>
GARDEN GROVE MAN ESCAPES SERIOUS INJURIES IN FIERY TRUCK ACCIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Garden Grove man escaped serious injuries early this morning when the truck 
he was driving at a high speed went out of control and broke apart before 
bursting into flames, Buena Park police officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Henry H. Herrera, 52, was thrown from his tractor-trailer near of La Palma and 
La Costa avenues, Police Lt. Gary Hicken said. 
</P>
<P>
"He apparently fell asleep," Hicken said before the truck hit a palm tree and 
flew into the air shortly before 1 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
Police investigators estimated that Herrera had been driving the truck along 
city streets in excess of 80 m.p.h. A test revealed that there was no alcohol 
in Herrera's bloodstream, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Officer Richard McMillen said the destruction resembled the aftermath of a 
plane crash. 
</P>
<P>
Herrera, who was found in a clump of nearby bushes, had a broken left arm and 
was taken to UCI-Medical Center in Orange, said hospital spokeswoman Fran 
Tardiff. 
</P>
</TEXT>
