<TEXT>
<P>
Playboy Enterprises Inc. today reported a fourth-quarter loss of more than $6 
million, compared to a $5.1-million loss in the same quarter last year. 
</P>
<P>
In the quarter ended June 30, Playboy reported revenues of $39.6 million 
compared to a $37.8-million loss in the fourth quarter of 1988. 
</P>
<P>
For the year ended June 30, Playboy reported a net loss of $3.8 million 
compared to a gain of $2.6 million the year before. 
</P>
<P>
"Fiscal 1989 was a year of significant accomplishments," said Christie Hefner, 
commenting on her first year-end results since taking over as chairman and 
chief executive officer in November. "While there was a cost to our actions 
which hurt fiscal 1989 results, we have appropriately and aggressively begun to 
make investments that will make this company grow in the '90s." 
