<P>
NUNN, BARKLEY WEIGH IN FOR THE TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
RENO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Michael Nunn weighed in at 159 pounds for his International Boxing Federation 
BF middleweight title defense tonight against Iran Barkley. Barkley weighed the 
class limit of 160. 
</P>
<P>
The scheduled 12-round bout was to be held at the Lawlor Events Center and 
televised by HBO. 
</P>
